# VS Code Can Do That
- https://burkeholland.gitbook.io/vs-code-can-do-that/essential-keyboard-shortcuts

## Shortcut faves
- command + , (settings)
- Open File Switcher - Cmd/Ctrl + P
- Opt + up or down moves the line
- Opt + shift arrow up or down to dup
- Command + opt [ or ] to FOLD
- Reg expression find + cursors > use ALT ENTER to start cursors

## Emmet faves
- `!` tab html boilerplate
- It is aware! ul>.yes*3 
- tag name than tab (div + tab) > <div></div>
```
<ul>
  <li class="yes"></li>
  <li class="yes"></li>
  <li class="yes"></li>
</ul>
```
- __Ctrl spacebar__ if emmet bugs out especially on grouping
- Grouping at same level ()+()
- emmet: outward / inward (opt + shift + [ or ])
- emmet: update image size (works on html and css)

## NPM
- `npm run` shows all you scripts
- npm enable run from script explorer: turn on :) 
- version lens - extensions 

## Finding things
- Command P - P last File
- Command P minus the > gets file picker
- Command @ - search doc structure
- Command @: - groups parts of doc
- Command @# - search across files
- Command + 0 - Sidebar Focus 
- Command + down to open sidebar focused file
- Command + 1 - Back to editor
- Rename everywhere F2
- Command + Ctrl + . > light bulb stuff
- //@ts-check > F8 move between errors or use `"javascript.implicitProjectConfig.checkJs": true`
- F5 - debugger

## Git
- Change line in theme to see change
- Ctrl + Shift + G > Source tab

## Debugging
- F5 - debugger
- Logging (log points) - Right click

## Debugging with Typescript
- Command Shift B -> typescript tasks
